  "description": "There\u0026rsquo;s a really cool critique of Byung-Chul Han that\u0026rsquo;s out, and that\u0026rsquo;s useful because Han and I are pretty similar theorists, but with very different backgrounds and underlying ideologies. And I\u0026rsquo;m going through it, and I\u0026rsquo;m comparing what Han is saying to my ecclesiastical studies.\nBasically Han (and others) are finding that the melancholy of the left might be the necessary precondition for non-optimistic hope, and they view this hope as the solution to the paralysis of melancholy.\n",
